title: The distribution of lead fission fragments by 7-Li ions at 35 MeV/A energy.

x4freetext: The distribution of lead fission fragments by 7-Li ions
at 35 MeV/A energy.

x4codes.hlp: A.I. Alikhanyan National Sci. Lab. (YerPhI), Yerevan, Armenia
Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna
Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4freetext: Short report
The paper which has been
submited to Yadernaya Fizika was received.
Irradiation time was 40 min.
Stack of 7 lead foils with thickness = 12
micrometers was used.  Aluminium plates with thickness
= 20 micrometers were disposed between lead foils.
The measurements were executed during to 3
months.

x4code.actHelp: Data received at the data center

x4freetext: Data table and total text of paper have
been received from N.A.Demekhina.
Last checking has been done.
The yields and kinematic characteristics of the
fission fragments have been measured for natural Pb
fission process by 7-Li ions with energy 35
MeV/nucleon.  Mass and charge distributions of the
fission fragments have been calculated by using the
approximation functions.  The measurements of the
ranges and recoil directions allow to obtain the
kinematic characteristics of the fission fragments and
fissioning nuclei.  The mean kinetic energies of the
fragments 140 MeV, approximately, are in a agreement
with Viola estimates.  The mean transferred
longitudinal momentum have been indicate on the part of
the projectile nucleons fusionning with the target
nucleus in initial process.  The fissibility of the
compound nucleus 0.8 (approximately) has been
calculated by using fission cross section and
interaction total cross section.
